      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) and normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) are the primary regulatory QOIs for CPB device submissions. Both are directly computed from CFD shear stress history using the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model. Direct correspondence to 510(k) acceptance criterion RH < 1 confirmed."
